  <priority-name nil="true"></priority-name>
  <original-body>ActiveSupport::JSON.decode automatically parses datestrings in json to Time objects, but fails to do so with xmlschema datetime notation (e.g. &quot;2009-08-10T19:34:24+02:00&quot;). Instead it returns a string rather than a Time object.

This used to work in rails 2.1.2, before the json gem/yaml backend split.

I've added 3 test cases (utc, positive and negative time zone) and a very simple fix in the date regexp (which adds the eventual T between date and time in the regexp).</original-body>
